description: - Serve as the 782nd Battalion network, engineering, and implementation technical specialist within the Battalion S-6 - Perform technical network analysis to assist end users to successfully utilize products and capabilities needed to carry out the Battalion's intelligence functions - Provide modernization, operation, and maintenance of classified and unclassified Local Area Network (LAN) and Wide Area Network (WAN) enterprise - Assess trends and find solutions when deficiencies in equipment, networks, or circuit operations are suspected - Provide technical advice and manage networks to ensure compatibility with other LAN and WAN architecture and all other Battalion networks at varying levels of classification - Coordinate with theater and high-level national agencies such as Defense Information Services Agency (DISA), Defense Intelligence Agency (DIA), and National Security Agency (NSA), to resolve any communication issues affecting the mission of the Cyber Battalion - Configure, utilize and analyze LAN and WAN communications status using various network monitoring tools and test equipment - Utilize telecommunications test equipment to measure and interpret various parameters such as bit error rate, packet loss, timing or framing problems, bandwidth utilization, and other indicators to measure network activity - Configure, maintain, and troubleshoot cryptographic systems - Establish LAN and WAN connections in accordance with DISA procedures as outlined in DISA circulars and regulations - Network Help Desk for routers, switches and all network devices

description: Assigned to Army Regional Computer Emergency Response Team. Responsibilities included ensuring the survivability of Army computer systems and networks against attacks aimed at disrupting services, gaining unauthorized access, or violating the integrity of data on Army information systems. Report all incidents to the Army Computer Emergency Response Team Coordination Center.

description: Primary duties include establishing CACU's Information Security Management Program, creating a functional, testable, and applicable Business Continuity / Disaster Recovery (BC/DR) program, and establishing an effective Service Provider Management program. *Information Security Developed, implemented and monitored a strategic, comprehensive enterprise information security and IT risk management program to ensure that the integrity, confidentiality and availability of information. Managed security incidents and events to protect corporate IT assets, including intellectual property, regulated data and the company's reputation. Provided strategic risk guidance for IT projects, including the evaluation and recommendation of technical controls. In conjunction with the IT director, assisted in the development of an enterprise wide Change Control Management Process. Implemented and operated an enterprise wide security informant and event manager (SIEM) at three physically separate locations. *Business Continuity / Disaster Recovery Lead functional units in conducting Business Impact Analysis and in creating Business Continuity Plans (BCP) for each business function, including the establishment of RTO/RPO. Successfully implemented and tested all functional unit and management BCPs including two actual weather based activations of the BCPs. Lead Business Continuity Meetings with senior management for the purposes of establishing policy, allocating personnel, and sufficient financial resources to properly implement the BCP; Ensured employees were trained and aware of their roles; regular testing of the BCP on an enterprise-wide basis; ensured the BCP was continually updated to reflect the current operating and business environment. Developed and implemented a staff training program for Business Continuity and Information Security CACU's staff on these policies.

description: Managed the daily operations of the Information Security SIEM solutions (LogRhythm) and ensured compliance of network assets. Identified, evaluated, and analyzed IT security requirements. Researched and implemented necessary solutions for the protection of all information processed, stored, or transmitted by information systems. Utilized detection tools to determine vulnerability status of all network assets. Used independent decision making to implement and assess security policies, procedures and practices for IT infrastructure, information, and internet/intranet connectivity throughout the enterprise. Acted as the system owner for SIEM and Identity Management processes, assisted with the development of information security policy and process. Developed a technical framework to provide information security metrics for the status of the information security program and ISO 2700x compliance. Worked closely with all business units and IT functions to establish effective enterprise security solutions. Instrumental in the development of effective disaster recovery and business continuity plans for the enterprise.

description: Responsible for the enclave security of three classified and one unclassified military networks. Planned, organized, developed, and provided oversight and alignment of security systems, continuity/disaster recovery plans and IT resiliency across multiple geographically dispersed sites. Established and implemented governance, best practice methodologies and tools relevant to Information Security. Developed, documented, maintained and oversaw compliance for IT security-related Policies and Procedures. Project Lead for the Continuity of Operations Plan (COOP) and Disaster Recovery (DR) Plan for the European Security Operations Center. Analyzed and evaluated designs and plans for DoD and DoD contractor systems and networks for compliance with automated information system security policies and requirements. Provided identification of specific security strengths, vulnerabilities, feasibility, costs and associated issues. Responsible for designing and coordinating the certification and training program (DoDD 8500.2 and DoDD 8570.01-M) for the IT workforce and tracking and monitoring annual IA training and workforce certification. Reviewed all proposed and new systems including software for potential security risks. Experienced with McAfee (AV and HBSS), Symantec AV, Bluecoat, Checkpoint FW, Retina, Wire Shark, SNORT, Python 3.

description: Developed and implemented all Physical Security, Personnel Security, Operational Security, and Information Security requirements related to the Deployed Digital Training Campus (DDTC). description: Developed, monitored, and issued classified contract and subcontract DD254s and Security Classification Guides (SCG). Instrumental in the development and implementation of a Corporate Proprietary Information Protection Program. Appointed ISSM for 7 classified systems utilizing both Windows and Linux operating systems. Granted self-certification authority for Protection Level 1 AISs utilizing Windows Operating systems by the Defense Security Service (DSS). Utilized NISPOM, NISPOM Overprint, JFAN 6/3, DCID 6/3 and 6/9 as applicable to AISs. Provided IA training and established Security Policy and Procedure for multiple programs with oversight/support to remote site security offices. Responsible for the development, implementation, and testing of DR and COOP plan. Facility Security Officer (FSO) for a wholly owned subsidiary (Pioneer UAV, Inc.) in a Joint Venture with a Foreign Owned Corporation. Responsible for all aspects of Personnel Security (JPAS/JCAVS included), Physical Security, Classified Contract Administration, and Security Administration. Issued SF 328s, DD 441s, and other Documents required under FOCI mitigation as needed.

description: Appointed Information Systems Security Officer (ISSO) for three classified networks and one classified stand alone periods processing system. Administered three classified and one unclassified Windows 2000 Advanced Server Domains consisting of over 150 computers. Duties included but were not limited to planning, implementing and maintaining active directory services, group policies, DNS, WINS, DHCP, and Server Configuration. Configured all systems through the use of domain security policies and group policy objects in accordance with NISPOM Chapter 8 and DSS guidelines. Conducted periodic self-inspections to ensure a strong network security policy. Reviewed Security Audit Logs to identify unauthorized access and activities. Conducted user network security training. Sanitized and disposed of classified equipment. Instituted safeguards and countermeasures ensuring confidentiality, integrity, and availability of information assets. Responsible for the configuration, and maintenance of a MS Exchange 2000 Server. Primary Help Desk point of contact for all end user issues related to email, connectivity, corporate intranet access, new user account creations, account terminations, Microsoft Outlook configuration and troubleshooting, and end user account maintenance. Monitored baseline management, technical, and operational controls of Departmental applications and general support systems. Responsible for drafting System Security Plans (SSP) for three classified computer networks and one stand alone periods processing system in accordance with Chapter 8 of the NISPOM. Configured local and domain security policies on clients and servers to conform to the SSPs. Successfully accredited three classified computer networks for classified operations with the DSS. Responsible for purchasing and tracking life cycle cost of equipment and materials. Implemented software license tracking procedures.

description: Served as a Voice Interceptor on a four man Special Operations Team-Alpha (SOT-A) team in support of 7th Special Forces Group which is oriented toward Central and South America with missions in Operation Enduring Freedom; executed counter-narcotics and counter-terrorist SIGINT missions in support of real-world operations in hostile and denied environments; employed portable collection equipment in overt, covert, urban, and tactical environments; performed initial processing of time-sensitive reports of actionable intelligence; provided individual and team training. Trained on Digital Receiver Technology (DRT) Systems, AN/PSC-5C Shadowfire, and various SIGINT collection systems; Completed three months of structured Spanish Language training to better augment his team's necessary skill set; completed 20K ruck march with 55lbs in three hours and 25 minutes During entire tour recieved an AAM Impact award and an AAM for PCS Award. Also, earned the Irish Parachutist Wings Foriegn Badge.

description: Process Engineer. In support of the Extended Shared Enterprise Corporate Servers Working Group (ESECS), met with business workflow owners to gather requirements, identify and document mission-critical workflow processes, determined customer’s needs and concerns migrating to thousands of documents and critical business workflows to another system. Senior Project Manager. Managed three highly-sensitive special projects: 1) Command Cyber Readiness Inspection Team; 2) designed, developed and deployed a congressionally mandated infrastructure which communicated directly with the U.S. Treasury utilizing specialized software; and 3) selected to serve on the Enterprise Collaboration Service Working Group, which is an inter-agency working group whose purpose is to identify and highlight the best practices in collaboration technologies across the IC, DoD and Mission Partner enterprises. Served as the Agency’s representative on the Intelligence Communities Common Operating Environment and Desktop Environment Committees. Systems Engineer. Successfully deployed custom developed software and hardware in various regions throughout the United States and in Europe. Designed, configured, implemented and managed a complex financial infrastructure which communicated directly with another financial institution. Designed work processes, authored and maintained system engineering documentation to ensure processes and specifications meet system needs and were accurate, comprehensive and complete. Managed system configuration requirements; coordinated efforts of internal and external software engineers and other stakeholders to ensure systems were developed according to design specifications; met system delivery milestones and within schedule deadlines. Wrote standard operating procedures for system configuration and management, CONOPS and Statements of Work. Transitioned thick client machines to thin clients.

description: Project Manager. Developed, oversaw, and maintained a project management function associated with the coordination of communications, meetings and events coordination, and facility research. Determined project requirements and assigned staff. Developed systems and processes necessary for the recruitment, tracking, planning and execution of projects. Ensured completion of deliverables and adherence to timelines. Tracked milestones and timelines across projects and instituted necessary work flow, personnel, and financial resource allocations, making alterations when necessary to meet expectations of clients. Analyzed and resolved issues that could jeopardize performance and/or the ability to meet agreed upon deliverables. Analyzed financial and operational reports. Identified changes in work scope and ensured appropriate planning measures were taken with internal and external clients to reassess, renegotiate, and amend scope of work responsibilities, proposals, contracts, and budgets. Analyzed short- and long-term resource needs and adjusted staffing and resources as appropriate. Oversaw and maintained liaison between all parties concerned with the project to facilitate any changes or modifications and to facilitate resolution of project problems.

description: Project Manager (Maryland Department of Transportation). Defined project scope, planned major project phases/milestones, coordinated activities across several delivery teams and established success factors. Defined and developed processes to manage and report on thousands of complex network projects within the Maryland Department of Transportation (MDOT) HQ and seven MDOT agencies using Microsoft Access and Microsoft Project. Participated in high-level MDOT Configuration Control Board meetings. Defined, developed and implemented Web links to Microsoft Access files, which produced more efficient project tracking and reporting systems. Served as liaison between client management, program manager and project groups. Produced and delivered project deliverables to multiple MDOT customers describing and supporting costs and expenses related to the multimillion-dollar MDOT contract. Transformed status reports from over 50 staff and subcontractors into a useful reporting tool for management and multiple customers. Designed and produced weekly, monthly and annual reports for senior management and principal customers. Monitored and motivated project team members’ work performance; directly supervised nine employees.

description: Intelligence Community Operations Program/Project Manager. Prepared briefs presented to a 4-Star General, prepared and disseminated daily, weekly and monthly Intelligence Summaries, shift supervisor during several major exercises including “Team Spirit” the world’s largest command post exercise; produced and accounted for over 30,000 documents annually. Highly visible Intelligence Center visited by Republic of Korea/US high-ranking service members including the President of Korea. Coordinated operational efforts to support counterdrug operations in 19 Latin American countries resulting in the seizure of thousands of tons of cocaine seizures. The Operations Center became a showcase for Ambassadors, Senators and several other VIPs. Supervised five civilian secretaries, one Navy Petty Officer and Two Army Staff Sergeants. • Administrative Manager/Writer. Internal Control Coordinator. Developed tickler system to track incoming and outgoing OPNAV/SECNAV and command correspondence, wrote Standard Operating Procedures (SOP), performance evaluations, awards, notices, instructions, policies and directives. Wrote sports articles for the Maryland Independent Newspaper.

description: Here is a brief description of the jobs I have carried out in this career field in chronological order, beginning with the most recent: *Aug 2014 - Current: Student at the Naval War College in Newport, Rhode Island. While earning my Masters of Arts in National Security and Strategic Studies, I am also earning the Information Operations Additional Qualification Designator. *Sep 2011 - Jul 2014: Exercise and Campaign Plans Chief as well as USEUCOM/USAFRICOM Information Technology Watch Chief under the Defense Intelligence Agency at RAF Molesworth, England. I held two separate jobs during my tenure there. The more recent one included the responsibility of supporting IT requirements for Exercises and Campaigns for both USAFRICOM and USEUCOM. The previous one included overseeing 28 servicemembers across the Army, Navy, and Air Force operating a 24-hour Help Desk that was responsible for IT issues for over 13,000 users. While there I also attended the National Intelligence University and earned my Masters of Science in Strategic Intelligence. *Sep 2010 - Sep 2011: Information Assurance Manager aboard the USS Emory S. Land (AS-39) homeported in the British Indian Ocean Territory island of Diego Garcia. Here I managed a total of 32 Information Technology specialists operating and maintaining 4 networks with a total of over 300 workstations. While there I also earned both my Information Dominance Warfare Officer breast insignia and my Certified Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP) certification. *Aug 2008 - Jun 2010: Student at the Naval Postgraduate School in Monterey, California. While I earned my Masters of Science in Joint Command, Control, Computers, Communications, and Intelligence Systems, I also earned all of the following certificates: Systems Engineering, Information Systems Security Professional, Systems Administrator, Information Systems Security Officer, Space Systems, Knowledge Superiority, and Information Systems and Operations.

description: Here is a brief description of the jobs I have carried out in this career field in chronological order, beginning with the most recent: *May 2005 - Dec 2007: Student at The Citadel, the Military College of South Carolina. While earning my Bachelors of Science in Business Administration, I am also earned minors in both Spanish and International Relations. I was selected as the Charleston Marine Containers, Inc. scholar of 2006 and the South Carolina International Trade Conference Scholar of 2007. I was inducted into the following National Honor Societies: Phi Kappa Phi (multi-disciplinary), Beta Gamma Sigma (Business), and Sigma Delta Pi (Spanish). *Aug 2004 - May 2005: I was a student at both the Broadened Opportunity for Officer Select Trainees (BOOST) and Naval Science Institute (NSI) at the Officer Training Command in Newport, Rhode Island. *May 2001 - Jul 2004: I was the lead AN/SRQ-4 Hawklink technician on the USS Jarrett (FFG-33) homeported in the San Diego, California. While there I also earned specialties as a technician on the Information Friend or Foe (IFF) system, the AN/SPS-55 surface search navigational radar, and the AN/SPS-49 air search radar. I was selected as the USS Jarrett and Commander, Destroyer Squadron 21 Junior Sailor of the Year of 2003. I arrived as an E-3 and earned promotions to both E-4 and E-5 while there. I earned my Enlisted Surface Warfare Specialist breast insignia there as well. *May 2000 - May 2001: I was a student at the following schools in Great Lakes Naval Station, Illinois: Basic Training, Advanced Electronics Training Corps, and Electronics Technician "A" school.

description: Track and govern IT and IS activities according to strict policy guidelines, standards and Industry practices. Key Responsibilities: • Establish and manage the certified Information Security Management System (ISO 27001) and certification to SOC 2 including: - Project manager for establishing the ISMS system and certification process - Assess the various information security and privacy requirements - Conduct business risk assessment and mitigation control plans and execution - Support client and vendor contract reviews to assure proper security controls are in place - Manage the corrective and preventive actions (CAPA) process, breach notification process, disaster recovery/business continuity program, and other incident management procedures - Manage the documentation and records management processes and outputs, which serve as evidence during ISO audits and certifications - Control applicable budgets - Inform senior management of quality system, security, and privacy initiatives and status • Evaluate and balance risk management objectives with business objectives. • Manage audit engagements, and the certification process across the business • Forecast and prepare for changes to future legislation affecting consumer medical data and general privacy legislation • Be the primary point of contact for all information security and privacy issues • Represent Caradigm in client and vendor discussions involving information security management • Conduct security and privacy reviews with product development teams • Create and maintain all information security training, including content, schedule, and records • Establish and maintain a network of security and privacy compliance champions within the organization to ensure controls are embedded and practices are followed throughout the development and operations lifecycles • Provide periodic reports on the effectiveness of the company’s information security management system to senior management

I helped found and continue to host the Infragard Digital Forensics Working Group which meets monthly to talk about technical topics in incident response and forencics. description: Escaped from hometown near Cleveland, Ohio to take on Information Security responsibilities in a different business vertical, in a warmer climate. Initially responsible for Information Security. Responsibilities expanded to include IT Disaster Recovery, and IT Procurement activities corporate wide. Built a team charged with providing security services associated with firewall management, malicious code control, security consulting, vulnerability protection, intrusion detection, incident management, forensics, user ID and application security administration, security infrastructure support, internet and email content filtering, and administration of the Information Security policy. Refined the Disaster Recovery program with new emphasis due to 9/11. Developed an IT Procurement program to achieve cost saving targets.

description: Managed the Corporate Information Security and Business Recovery Division within Key Services Corporation. Lead the mission to provide for the control, safekeeping, and recoverability of the Bank’s electronic information assets and systems. The responsibility extended Corporate-wide to include all KeyCorp banking and non-banking affiliates covering the organization’s geographic span from coast to coast. Joined Society Corporation (now KeyCorp) as a senior programmer in the Corporate Information Security Department. Lead various projects that reengineered and automated processes to replace routine tasks. Was a Project Manager for the Trustcorp, Ameritrust, and Society/KeyCorp mergers. Developed several processes that were used to automate the conversion/migration of the security systems. Promoted several times to positions of increased responsibility. In 1995, assumed responsibility for the Corporate Information Security and Business Recovery department and was appointed Vice President for the division.

description: • Make proactive assessments of threat information in and outside the public domain, understanding the threat as it relates to T-Mobile and its customers, and implementing measures to combat the threat. • Understand the operations of the business and comprehend how these create value and risk for the organization. • Collaborate with team members, peers and the business unit management team to determine technical information security requirements, planned remediation, and advocate for the program to gain resources to implement appropriate protection technologies and processes. • Implement and monitor controls necessary to ensure operational processes are performed and are effective to protect the environment from all forms of malicious cyber activity. • Assist the Governance group in the development and refinement of technical security standards, key performance indicators and other necessary processes to maintain effective operational security, as it relates to the business. • Make risk-based decisions on a daily basis that has the potential to impact T-Mobile's ability to operate and communicate. • Ensure the information and network security controls for T-Mobile are appropriate and operating as intended; includes solutions that are directly controlled as well as security solutions that are operated by other internal and external groups. • Provide status reports on a weekly, monthly and quarterly basis to business managers and other management activities that demonstrate the health of the program. • Interact with internal audit, third party auditors, and appropriate regulatory bodies. • Support the Information Security policy lifecycle throughout, including all aspects of intake, creation, review, approval, implementation, publishing, communication and maintenance. • Liaise with and assist outsourced security service providers with vulnerability assessments of business applications, systems and architectures.

description: Hired to take on the challenge of creating and managing a national, corporate-wide vulnerability management program and provide vision on project security support functions. This work included brokering close partnerships with Business and IT management teams to integrate security assessment & vulnerability management processes and technologies with existing Enterprise Projects Office and IT operations. To provide focus on these goals existing security and IT services were restructured and consolidated into the following areas of Vulnerability and Project Security Support Management: • IT Security as a Service • Self-Service Host and Application Scanning Service Management • SDLC/Agile Security Lifecycle Management Testing • Project Security Support, Tracking, Management and Reporting • Complete Security Support Portfolio for Projects • Managed Security Service Provider with SLAs • Secure Configuration Benchmark Implementation and Testing • Vulnerability Management Governance • Initiated departmental security leads for the individual business units within the IT organization to reduce operational security expenses. • Developed and operationalized a strong, measurable, corporate-wide, national vulnerability management program and organization to improve project delivery time and customer satisfaction. • Integrated people, process and technology to identify, evaluate, and protect against information security vulnerabilities while ensuring security processes support successful, competitive delivery of enterprise and mobile products, software and services to T-Mobile customers. • Developed and aligned activities related to supporting the identification, prioritization, remediation and reporting of information technology vulnerabilities at T-Mobile to achieve corporate/shareholder objectives while enabling PCI, SOX and CPNI compliance and conformance with contractual security obligations and internal security requirements.

description: Established and maintained an enterprise-wide vision, strategy, architecture, and program for ensuring information assets are appropriately protected across the Department’s enterprise and technology stack. Ensured compliance with all applicable US federal and state laws, directives, policies and securing of information. Oversaw implementation of the information security plans, and managed the operational processes for monitoring and maintaining information security. Lead and directed proactive Cybersecurity activities in ensuring the Department had effective and consistent controls to ensure sound information and cyber protection through real threat monitoring, incident response and Security Program Management to meet changes in a rapidly evolving environment. Developed, implemented and monitored a strategic, comprehensive enterprise Cybersecurity and risk management program to ensure the integrity, confidentiality and availability of information owned, controlled or processed by the Department. Collaborated with key business and IT leaders to develop and implement security and business continuance standards and action plans to achieve regulatory obligations, minimize risk and drive strategies to ensure data protection. Acted as the Department's advocate/advisor for information security and business continuance best practices.Consulted with senior IT and business leaders regarding their information security risks and responsibilities in minimizing those risks. Managed security incidents and events to protect Department IT assets, including intellectual property, regulated data and the Department's reputation. Ensured the development, publishing and maintenance of comprehensive information security standards, policies, procedures and guidelines. Developed and managed staff through staffing/terminations, performance management process, promotions, etc. to support information security strategies and direction.

description: • Maintained the workload and mentoring of two security specialists directly assigned to support this position. • Established processes for information asset classification and ownership, and implement a systematic, structured information risk assessment process. • Integrated risk, threat, vulnerability identification and management into the life cycle process. • Developed information security architecture patterns including people, processes, and technologies that integrate into the Department s processes such as change control, capital planning, application development and procurement. • Established, communicated and maintained information security policies, standards and guidelines that support the security strategy and establish metrics to evaluate the effectiveness of the information security program. • Developed and implement processes for detecting, identifying, analyzing and responding to information security incidents and established escalation, communication processes and lines of authority. • Organized, trained, and equipped technology teams with the knowledge and procedures required to effectively respond to information security incidents. • Conducted reviews to identify causes of information security incidents, developed corrective action plans, and reassessed risk after incidents.

description: • Served as a technical expert and adviser performing network and configuration security management compliance, network security administration, and customer support functions. • Supervised a group of five military personnel to support network operations and security for the unit. • Ensured the maintenance and security of network operations and configuration management compliance and resolved problems concerning networks, computers, peripherals and services. • Ensured that security policies were built into system life-cycles and established measures for security compliance. • Designed, deployed and maintained Microsoft s Systems Management Server (SMS) utilizing most of the available features to over 8000 critical organizational computer systems and servers. • Managed the upgrade from SMS 2003R2 to SCCM 2007 (SMS V4) architecture. • Established and maintained computer and network security procedures and guidelines. • Provided technical advice and assistance to users, provided formal/informal training to users and IT Staff, and performed other related duties as requested.

description: I lead 3-day workshops for retiring and separating military personnel from all services. Through instruction and practical exercises, workshop attendees learn about job search strategies, career decision-making, current labor market conditions, resume preparation, interview techniques and salary negotiation. It is wonderful to serve those who have served by helping prepare them for life after the military. This is incredibly rewarding work—I love my job!

description: I was approached and delighted to take on the role of Director of Programs for an 8 month period while the Executive Director was on Maternity Leave. In Gear Career is an inspirational non-profit organization which improves the quality of life for military families by enabling military spouses to seek and obtain professional employment. I thoroughly enjoyed the opportunity to contribute to their valuable work by developing their new website resources.

description: I coordinated the Family Employment Program for an overseas military installation supporting 2700 military personnel from all services and over 3500 spouses and dependents. I found it incredibly rewarding to provide individual career counseling, job search assistance, and resume development services transitioning military personnel, spouses and school students. Highlights included: ★ Facilitating a highly successful series of employment classes including "Ten Steps to a Federal Job," "Resume Writing," and "Interview Skills" on a monthly basis. ★ Becoming the subject matter expert on the local labor market and providing referrals and job search assistance for military personnel and family members seeking public and private sector positions in all US States and abroad.

description: Troop Senior Operations Specialist responsible for leading a five-member team in the identification and analysis of current and emerging asymmetric threats to US national security. Regularly brief senior military commanders and civilian executives on study insights directly affecting execution of the National Security Strategy and the White House Strategy to Combat Transnational Organized Crime. Expertly led numerous studies and co-authored and edited three strategic-level analyses and several professional publications for the DoD used to inform campaign planning and the strategic operations of US DoD, DoS, DHS and NATO regarding threats to US national security in East Africa, the Middle East and Southeast Asia.

description: The Asymmetric Warfare Group (AWG) provides operational advisory assistance in support of Army and Joint Force Commanders to enhance the combat effectiveness of the operating force and enable the defeat of asymmetric threats.The AWG is designed to improve the asymmetric warfare capabilities of the U. S. Army at the operational and tactical levels throughout the full spectrum of conflict. AWG enhances the capabilities of U.S. units by making them faster and more adept at identifying and attacking enemy vulnerabilities, and by preparing them for a broader spectrum of threats.

It's two major research thrusts, leading edge computer simulation research and current military operations research problems, ensure the Center remains relevant and closely linked with the Army. TRAC-Monterey is recognized as a premier applied research organization for military modeling, simulation, methodologies, and analysis.

description: • Co-Founder of Dawning Valley, an online publication created for top quality technology content, 2008-2009. Managed permanent staff of six contributors. Made Slashdot. • Freelance journalist for Mashable.com, 2007-2008 (23 million unique visitors/month). • Freelance journalist, Linux Journal, 2008-2008 (print magazine, monthly circulation of 90,000). • Freelance journalist, Linux.com, a Sourceforge Inc. subsidiary, 2007-2009 (1 million unique visitors/month). • Columnist and Proofreader, Full Circle Magazine, 2007-2011 (online Ubuntu magazine averaging 20,000-60,000 views/month). • Columnist, Free Software Magazine, 2007-2008 (online free software publication with 20,000 views/issue), 2007-2008. Advised the founder on company strategy and promotion/marketing. Invited to be a judge on the Free Software Magazine Awards panel. • Columnist, Newsvine.com (MSNBC.com subsidiary), 2007-2009. Wrote technology and politics column averaging 6500+ visitors a month. Invited by MSNBC.com to cover the 2008 Republican National Convention.
